ter $\\omega \\gtrsim 3300$\nand the Gauss-Bonnet coupling parameter $\\alpha^{1/2} \\lesssim 0.5 \\;\n{\\rm{km}}$ at 90% confidence. Although the projected constraint on $\\omega$ is\nweaker than other current constraints, the projected constraint on\n$\\alpha^{1/2}$ is 10 times stronger than the current gravitational wave bound.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Feb 2020 20:59:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-26"}
